--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages iproute.

The iproute package contains networking utilities (ip and rtmon, for example)
which are designed to use the advanced networking capabilities of the Linux
2.4.x and 2.6.x kernel.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: iproute
       iproute_state: 'install'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: iproute
       iproute_state: 'remove'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  iproute_state
    Specify predetermined 'iproute_state' variable (string).
    Notice: 'iproute' is a core package on RedHat and CentOS based systems and
    can therefore not be removed.

    Install: 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
    Remove : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'
    Default: 'install'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DEPENDENCIES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

PACKAGES
  iproute: >= 2.6
    CentOS, RedHat

  iproute2: >= 3.8
    Gentoo

